
app/ Contais the controllers, models, views, helpers, mailers, and assets for your application. You'll focus on this folder.

bin/ Contains the Rails scriptthat starts your apps and can contain other scripts you use to setup or run your application

config/ configure your application routes, database, and more. 

config.ru/Rack configuration for Rack based servers used to start the application.

db/ Contains your current database schema, as well as the database migrations

Gemfile and Gemfile.lock These files alow you to specify what gem dependencies are needed for your rails application. This files are 
used by Bundler gem. 

lib/ Extended modules for your application.

log/ Application log files.

public/ The only folder seen by the world as-in. Contain static files and compiled assets.

rakefile This files locates and load tasks that can be run from the command line the task definitions and defined throughout the 
components of Rails. Rather then changing Rakefile you should add your own tasks by adding files to the bin/tasks directory of your 
application.

README.rdoc This is a brief introduction manual for your application. You should edit this file to tell others what your application
does, how to set it up, and so on.





